  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.6\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ngeth creates a pruned (no state data) copy of the ropsten blockchain\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\ngeth aborts with error `err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`$ geth --datadir=/mnt/chaindata/newchain copydb --cache=2048 /mnt/chaindata/geth/chaindata/`\r\n\r\nLike many others I've found issue #15797 and used it to keep my storage requirements for full nodes down.\r\n\r\nCopy-and-pasting the command above onto my `mainnet` nodes it works perfectly (well, geth crashes several times during the whole process and has to be restarted but does eventually complete, however that is another ticket). But on my `ropsten` nodes the `copydb` command won't even begin.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n$ geth --datadir=/mnt/chaindata/newchain copydb --cache=2048 /mnt/chaindata/geth/chaindata/\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/mnt/chaindata/newchain/geth/chaindata cache=1536 handles=1024\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Disk storage enabled for ethash caches   dir=/mnt/chaindata/newchain/geth/ethash count=3\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Disk storage enabled for ethash DAGs     dir=/home/coinnode/.ethash              count=2\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Loaded most recent local header          number=0 hash=d4e567…cb8fa3 td=17179869184\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Loaded most recent local full block      number=0 hash=d4e567…cb8fa3 td=17179869184\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Loaded most recent local fast block      number=0 hash=d4e567…cb8fa3 td=17179869184\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/mnt/chaindata/geth/chaindata/         cache=2048 handles=256\r\nINFO [04-27|22:02:01] Block synchronisation started \r\nWARN [04-27|22:02:02] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=local err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\nWARN [04-27|22:02:02] Downloader wants to drop peer, but peerdrop-function is not set peer=local\r\nretrieved hash chain is invalid\r\n````\r\n",
